  "text": "The revised model has one more hazard. When Cln3 becomes 1, it enables both MBF and SBF to transition from 0 to 1. But Cln3 inhibits itself, so it can return to 0 before either SBF or MBF changes, causing the cell cycle to arrest. The hazard can be eliminated by replacing self-degradation of Cln3 with inhibition by SBF and MBF, so that SBF and MBF both must change before Cln3 returns to 0. As observed in Orlando, et al. [CITATION_1] , MBF and SBF indirectly inhibit Cln3 by activating Yox1 and Yhp1.",
